         <abstract id="aspace_fcfff9e50ce49a7b3227b18ab1db0dfe">A collection of correspondence; writings; and published illustrated materials from and about Brazil related to Imperial Brazil, religious, economic, and geographic concerns. There is one item under the heading Portugal: a letter of condolence upon the death of a distant relative of Vasco de Gama.</abstract>
         <langmaterial id="aspace_e06b67a760f4ba531b5f9be28f18e875">
            <language>The collection is in Portuguese, English, and Italian.</language>
         </langmaterial>
    
      </did>
      <altformavail id="aspace_0bc5f7d06e91c15416da4a50da8625b1">
         <head>Existence and Location of Copies</head>
         <p>The entire collection, with the exception of Accession 2013-M-024, is available on microfilm from Gale Group, Farmington Hills, Michigan.</p>  
      </altformavail>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_b8006d1ac7b40ed1b2d1359424b39a8c">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Materials have been assembled from various collections and acquired from several individuals. They include materials transferred from the Latin American Collection Curator, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_66690b79d17e6005acb19818e66fa208">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>
         <p>The entire collection, with the exception of Accession 2013-M-024, is available on microfilm. Patrons must use FILM HM 254 instead of the originals.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_4922d7837133009359d2704c7ee5ae6c">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright status for collection materials is unknown, though much of the material in this collection is likely in the public domain. Transmission or reproduction of materials protected by U.S. Copyright Law (Title 17, U.S.C.) beyond that allowed by fair use requires the written permission of the copyright owners. Works not in the public domain cannot be commercially exploited without permission of the copyright owners. Responsibility for any use rests exclusively with the user.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_bbd6585b742fe79a71022dfc8ee3c05d">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Brazil and Portugal Collection (MS 1781). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <arrangement id="aspace_ab2bc660fb075942f24e201a6f417d19">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The collection is arranged alphabetically by country, and by date within the country, and one accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_98778ae3ed41c9b0014803337ed8d4ff">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection is comprised of correspondence; writings; and published illustrated materials from and about Brazil, and is arranged by date. The description of each item includes, when possible, its author, title, place of origin, and a summary of its contents. When an item is a copy of an original, it is arranged by the date of the original. The date field, however, contains the date of the copy itself, not the original. The date of the original is included in the summary description of the item.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
